    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Acute Myocardial Infarction (MI) confirmed by electrocardiographic and or/ enzymatic
             criteria

          -  Patients with a left ventricular ejection fraction of 45% or less

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with (1) atrial fibrillation, (2) pacemaker rhythm, (3) left bundle branch
             block, (4) class III-IV heart failure, (5) inability to achieve a target heart rate
             with exercise or handgrip stress or (6) spontaneous sustained ventricular
             tachycardia/ventricular fibrillation will be excluded

          -  Patients with recurrent angina pectoris, MI, coronary revascularization, or any other
             adverse cardiovascular event in the 30 days following their initial MI will also be
             excluded
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
